It is easy enough to bribe some 2,000 Members of the County Assembly with goodies pilfered from the public purse but quite a different proposition altogether when you have to contend with some 19 million or so registered voters. 

In any case, chances are that most of the MCAs who voted in favour of the referendum will not be enthusiastic boosters for the ‘Yes’ camp when it goes to the public campaigns. They might even turn outright hostile on discovery that the car grants promised to them by the President in exchange for support for the bill were an outright hoax. In this day and age, the President simply does not have an unfettered right to dish out public funds as he wishes. 



